				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="ウィッチズウィスク (Witches Whisk)" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#166;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#163;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#131;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#129;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#186;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#166;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#163;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#185;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#175; (Witches Whisk) is a game from Japan, with apprentice witches at a magic school flying on broomsticks over the sports field. The game can be played as a competitive game for a single winner by scoring victory points, or as a co-operative game trying to stop the escaping magical creatures. The main rules apply for both games and the co-op game can be played solo.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has a subtitle &amp;#239;&amp;#189;&amp;#158;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#184;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#167;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#172;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#159;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#162;&amp;#233;&amp;#173;&amp;#148;&amp;#230;&amp;#179;&amp;#149;&amp;#229;&amp;#173;&amp;#166;&amp;#230;&amp;#160;&amp;#161;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#174;&amp;#232;&amp;#168;&amp;#147;&amp;#231;&amp;#183;&amp;#180;&amp;#230;&amp;#179;&amp;#149;&amp;#239;&amp;#189;&amp;#158;(~Jeremiah Magic School Training Method~).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players use dice to place against three actions: Activating Magic, Movement, and Student Skills.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;By placing dice against the six different magic circuit cards, a player can gain magic spells from them. Magic is used when attacking other players, or the creatures. Dice used on the magic broom of a student allows the player to move that witch across the playing field. Each student has special skills which are used once per round with the dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends after six rounds. Players need to balance the development of their students, combining attack and defence, and movement and growth of skills. The more a student develops, the more they can achieve by the final round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In a 2 player game, each player controls two witches. In a co-operative game, players can pass on good dice rolls. In the competitive game, getting to be start player gives you advantages.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The second edition released in 2022 had improved components and box art, but the gameplay was the same.&amp;#10;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
